    "faq_XBijfr": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "accordion_9JmLm4": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How will the Qure Shower Filter benefit my hair/skin?",
            "text": "<p>The Qure Shower Filter removes harmful impurities like heavy metals, chlorine, and unwanted minerals from your water, helping to protect your skin and hair from damage caused by hard water.</p><p>By filtering out water impurities, the Qure Shower Filter helps reduce dryness, irritation, and brittleness, leaving your skin hydrated and your hair smoother and more manageable.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_qTTqKR": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Does the filter lose effectiveness over time?",
            "text": "<p>Yes, the filter removes up to 99% of chlorine initially, 95% after 4,000 liters, and 90% after 6,000 liters. For best results, we recommend replacing it after 5,000 liters (around 3 months).</p><p>We recommend replacing the filter every 3 months for optimal performance.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_BVDjUj": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How do I know when to replace the filter?",
            "text": "<p>A slight drop in water pressure or visible buildup on the filter may indicate it’s time for a replacement. We recommend changing it every 3 months to maintain optimal performance.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_tapruN": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How do I install the new filter refill?",
            "text": "<ul><li>Turn off the water.</li><li>Open the filter housing and remove the old cartridge.</li><li>Unwrap the new cartridge and insert it into the housing.</li><li>Secure the cover by screwing it back clockwise.</li><li>Turn on the water and let it run for 2–3 minutes to flush out any initial particles.</li></ul>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_T7q3Pd": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Is the Qure Shower Filter certified, tested, and safe to use?",
            "text": "<p>Yes — it’s third-party tested to meet NSF water filtration standards and made with certified BPA-free, non-toxic, and skin-friendly materials. It’s also leak-resistant and built to last.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_GqFLAt": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Where can I buy filter refills?",
            "text": "<p>You can purchase filter refills directly from our website, which provides 3 months of pure water. We also offer convenient subscription plans to ensure you never run out—set it and forget it, and we’ll take care of the rest.</p>",
            "link_url": "",
            "link_text": ""
          }
        }
      },
